Private Property has appointed Amasi Mwela as the company’s new chief executive officer, effective January 2 2019. According to a statement, the appointment comes at a time when the property company seeks to boost its own growth since changing ownership in February 2018. “The company is now poised to build on its strong growth while enhancing the role that technology can play in the real estate industry,” the statement read. Mwela joins Private Property after heading Fundi, where he led the company’s rebranding and introduced comprehensive solutions for the education sector, which included funding, fund administration, support and related products. Mwela previously worked for Old Mutal iWYZE, American Express Corporate Travel, First National Bank and Standard Bank. He holds a Bachelor of Commerce (Bond University) and has an MBA (Milpark Business School).